      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "Linear absolute value equations have two, one, or no solutions. The solution set for linear absolute value inequalities may contain all real numbers, a subset of the real numbers represented by a compound inequality, or no solutions.",
          "It is possible to rewrite linear absolute value inequalities as equivalent compound inequalities.",
          "Linear absolute value equations and inequalities can represent real-world situations."
        ]
